div.div: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken: Stardust Crusaders

In a Japanese jail sits 17-year-old Jotaro Kujo: punk, fighter, delinquent...and possessed by a force beyond his control! Around the world, evil spirits are awakening: "Stands," monstrous invisible creatures which give their bearers incredible powers. To save his mother's life, Jotaro must tame his dark forces and travel around the world to Cairo, Egypt, where a hundred-year-old vampire thirsts for the blood of his family. But the road is long, and an army of evil Stand Users waits to kill JoJo and his friends...
(Source: Viz Media)

Okajima Rokuro is a Japanese businessman in a town full of Japanese businessmen. His normal day consists of social drinking with clients and being kicked around by his bosses. He finally gets a break though, as he's sent by his company to the tropical seas of Eastern China to deliver a disc. But his boat gets hijacked by a band of mercenaries hired to retrieve the disc. Rock (as he is newly dubbed by his captors) catches the interest of the only female merc Revy as she thinks he's worth a ransom, taking him hostage. However, the disc that was stolen has a terrible secret that's unknown to Rock, which causes massive confusion and chaos for both him and his kidnappers.
JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken: Stardust Crusaders - Egypt-hen

After 30 days of travel across the world, plagued with countless battles, Jotaro and his companions have finally arrived in Egypt! Now only the strongest "Stand" users remain to rebuff our heroes' final march on Cairo: The Nine Egyptian Gods, Dio's most zealous servants. Will the Joestar line fall to the monstrous vampire, or can Jotaro defeat Dio and save his mother's life?
(Source: Crunchyroll)

A man working a job far removed from his childhood dreams gets wrapped up in an unexpected situation! Becoming a monster, he aims once again to fulfill his lifelong dream! (Source: MANGA Plus) Note: - Nominated for the 14thManga Taisho Award in 2021. - Winner of the 7th Next Manga Award in the Web Manga Category in 2021.

"In Manchuria, human life is worthless"

The year was Showa 12 (1937). Isamu Hinata, a soldier of the Kanto Army, arrived in Manchuria and lost his right eye on the battlefield. Deemed useless, he was reassigned to the agricultural corps, producing food for the army, while enduring daily abuse from his superiors. One day, he discovered poppies the raw material for the narcotic opium being cultivated in a corner of the farm. To help save his sick mother, Isamu began to refine opium. This fateful decision would set in motion events that would change both his own destiny and that of Manchuria itself

(Source: Comic Days, translated)
